Subtitle
15
16 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING
17 ABSENTEE BALLOTS; TO AMEND THE ABSENTEE
18 BALLOT VOTER STATEMENT; AND TO REQUIRE A
19 WITNESS FOR THE SIGNATURE OF AN ABSENTEE
20 VOTER STATEMENT.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 7-5-409(b)(4)(A)(iii), concerning the
25 materials furnished to qualified electors for absentee ballots, is amended to
26 read as follows:
27 (iii) The voter statement shall include the
28 following statement in bold capitalized letters at the bottom of the page: “I
29 AM DULY QUALIFIED TO VOTE AT THIS ELECTION ACCORDING TO THE ARKANSAS
30 CONSTITUTION, I HAVE NOT YET VOTED DURING THIS ELECTION, THE BALLOT OR
31 BALLOTS CONTAINED IN THIS ENVELOPE IS MY BALLOT, AND I HAVE RECEIVED NO
32 ASSISTANCE IN VOTING MY BALLOT THAT I WOULD NOT HAVE BEEN ENTITLED TO RECEIVE
33 HAD I VOTED IN PERSON AT MY VOTING PRECINCT. THE INFORMATION I HAVE PROVIDED
34 IS TRUE TO THE BEST OF MY KNOWLEDGE UNDER PENALTY OF PERJURY. IF I HAVE
35 PROVIDED FALSE INFORMATION, I MAY BE SUBJECT TO A FINE OF UP TO TEN THOUSAND
36 DOLLARS ($10,000) OR IMPRISONMENT FOR UP TO TEN (10) YEARS, OR BOTH, UNDER
