1 FEDERAL OR STATE LAWS.”
2
3 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 7-5-409(b)(4)(C), concerning the materials
4 furnished to qualified electors for absentee ballots, is amended to read as
5 follows:
6 (C)(i) The voter statement shall include a sworn statement
7 portion that may be completed by the voter stating that the voter is
8 registered to vote and that he or she is the person who is registered.
9 (ii) The sworn statement portion of the voter
10 statement is not required to be notarized, but the voter shall execute the
11 sworn statement under penalty of perjury.
12 (iii)(a) The signing of the sworn statement shall be
13 witnessed by at least one (1) individual who is eighteen (18) years of age or
14 older.
15 (b) The witnessing requirement under
16 subdivision (b)(4)(C)(iii)(a) of this section shall not apply to a voter who
17 has applied for his or her absentee ballot due to one (1) of the following,
18 as evidenced by his or her absentee voting application:
19 (1) The voter is unable to attend the
20 polls on election day because of an illness or physical disability;
21 (2) The voter is a resident of a long-
22 term care or residential facility licensed by the state;
23 (3) The voter is unable to attend the
24 polls on election day due to an observance of a religious discipline or
25 religious holiday; or
26 (4) The voter:
27 (a) Is in active service as a
28 member of the armed services of the United States or the voter is a spouse or
29 a dependent of a person who is in active service as a member of the armed
30 services of the United States; and
31 (b) Resides outside the county.
32 (D) Blank fields shall be provided for the witness of the
33 sworn statement's signature to provide his or her:
34 (i) Printed name;
35 (ii) Signature; and
36 (iii) Mailing address;
